<div id="v230.150.1"><span class="H1984 s">Praise</span><span class="H3050 s"> ye the LORD</span><span class="H1984 s">. Praise</span><span class="H410 s"> God</span><span class="H6944 s"> in his sanctuary</span><span class="H1984 s">: praise</span><span class="H7549 s"> him in the firmament</span><span class="H5797 s"> of his power</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (Praise yeâ€¦: Heb. Hallelujah)</span></div>
<div id="v230.150.2"><span class="H1984 s">Praise</span><span class="H1369 s"> him for his mighty acts</span><span class="H1984 s">: praise</span><span class="H7230 s"> him according to his excellent</span><span class="H1433 s"> greatness</span>.</div>
<div id="v230.150.3"><span class="H1984 s">Praise</span><span class="H8629 s"> him with the sound</span><span class="H7782 s"> of the trumpet</span><span class="H1984 s">: praise</span><span class="H5035 s"> him with the psaltery</span><span class="H3658 s"> and harp</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (trumpet: or, cornet)</span></div>
<div id="v230.150.4"><span class="H1984 s">Praise</span><span class="H8596 s"> him with the timbrel</span><span class="H4234 s"> and dance</span><span class="H1984 s">: praise</span><span class="H4482 s"> him with stringed instruments</span><span class="H5748 s"> and organs</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (dance: or, pipe)</span></div>
<div id="v230.150.5"><span class="H1984 s">Praise</span><span class="H8088 s"> him upon the loud</span><span class="H6767 s"> cymbals</span><span class="H1984 s">: praise</span><span class="H8643 s"> him upon the high sounding</span><span class="H6767 s"> cymbals</span>.</div>
<div id="v230.150.6"><span class="H5397 s">Let every thing that hath breath</span><span class="H1984 s"> praise</span><span class="H3050 s"> the LORD</span><span class="H1984 s">. Praise</span><span class="H3050 s"> ye the LORD</span>.</div></div>
